bilingual.source: If you fail, no problem – next time you can fail better!
bilingual.target: 如果你失败了，没关系——下次你可以失败得更好！

bilingual.source: What do you think Lisa means by "If you fail, no problem"?
bilingual.target: 你认为丽莎说的“如果你失败了，没关系”是什么意思？

bilingual.source: If you fail to plan, you plan to fail.
bilingual.target: 如果你失败于计划，你就是在计划失败。
失败准备就是准备失败。
他们的计划注定要失败。
我们不能让这个项目失败。
她认定这个计划会失败。

bilingual.source: It's okay to fail, just try again.
bilingual.target: 失败了没关系，再试一次。

bilingual.source: He was doomed to fail from the start.
bilingual.target: 他从一开始就注定要失败。

list.abstract: fail [feil]vi.失败， 不及格， 忘记vt.使失望， 舍弃， 辜负， 不及格n.不及格， 不及格者；必定，总是

yingyinNormal.en: I don't know. Maybe you wanted your marriage to fail.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不知道，或许你想让婚姻失败。

yingyinNormal.en: But it matters not. Oakenshield's quest will fail.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但无所谓橡，木盾的远征注定要失败。

yingyinNormal.en: The invasion will fail no matter how many bodies you throw at it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们注定失败，无论你让多少战士去送死。

yingyinNormal.en: If you're really one of us, it won't matter to you that you might fail.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果你真是无畏派的人，就会无视失败的可能。

yingyinNormal.en: We did not fail. And we are not running away. We're just very sensibly regrouping.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们没有失败，我们现在不是逃跑，我们只是在理智地重组。

yingyinNormal.en: I realized that if I fail to do that, I will be a failure. I struggle with this now.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果我做不到这一点我将是一个失败。这就是我现在的挣扎。

yingyinNormal.en: If you do, my program will fail. This could be a real weapon. It's worth risking my life.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果你动手，我的程序就会失败，这是真正的武器，值得我拿生命冒险。

yingyinNormal.en: The throne is mine and I will ascend to it. There is nothing I desire more than this. But you fear I will fail.
yingyinNormal.zh: 皇位是我的，我会顺利继承。这是我最希望看到的。但是您怕我会失败。

yingyinNormal.en: Lady Grantham is not as young as she was, and, as Mrs Crawley says, I'm afraid she'd be almost willing the new regime to fail. Probably.
yingyinNormal.zh: 老夫人没以前那么年轻了，正如卡劳利太太所说，恐怕她更乐意看到新系统失败。很有可能。

yingyinNormal.en: Our priority must be to stop the gate from opening. Fail there, and it's just a matter of time before they beat us with sheer numbers.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们必须优先阻止传送门打开，如果那里失败，在他们以绝对数量击败我们之前只是一个时间问题了。

yingyinNormal.en: If America Works succeeds, we will reinvent the American dream. If we fail in our attempt, we will admit it frankly and try another.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果美国就业法案成功了，我们将彻底改造美国梦，如果我们的尝试失败，我们会坦白承认，然后重新来过。

yingyinNormal.en: So you didn't like him. I loved him. Then why don't you teach like him? Because I would never try and be like him. I could only fail.
yingyinNormal.zh: 所以你不喜欢他。我太爱他了。那为什么不像他一样教书呢？因为我永远都无法做到他那个水平。我一定会失败的。

yingyinNormal.en: I want to not fail.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不想不及格。

yingyinNormal.en: Then you won't fail and then neither will I.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那你就不会不及格了。那我也不会被莱丽抛弃了。

yingyinNormal.en: I just don't want to fail, Mr. Matthews. Thank you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我只是不想不及格，麦修斯老师，谢谢。

yingyinNormal.en: And what if you fail to try, Peter? What are you then?
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果你不努力呢，彼得？那又会怎样？

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, I knew you couldn't. What? You set me up to fail? Why?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我就知道你不行。啥？你故意的吗？为什么？

yingyinNormal.en: When the majority of the adjustable rates kick in, in '07, they will begin to fail. And if they fail above 15%, the whole bond is worthless.
yingyinNormal.zh: 等大多数浮动利率在07年开始执行时他们就会开始下跌，如果下跌超过15%，整个债券就一文不值了。

yingyinNormal.en: What you fail to realize is Kripke suffers from a fatal flaw.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你没发觉的是克里帕奇有一个致命伤。

yingyinNormal.en: The point is my natural charisma has made him fail his midterm.
yingyinNormal.zh: 重点是我的自然魅力让他期中考试不及格。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

derivative_info_list.mean: n. 失败；未做到；未履行；故障；失灵；衰退；衰竭；缺乏；不足；公司倒闭

word_family.mean: v. 失败；忘记做；坏掉；不能正常工作；破产；衰退；消失；舍弃；变弱；在（考试、测验或面试）中不及格

sense_info_list.en: to not be successful in achieving sth

examination_example.sentence: Every time we <highlight>fail</highlight> at something, we can choose to look for the lesson we're meant to learn.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 每当我们在某件事上失败时，我们可以选择寻找我们应该学到的教训。

examination_example.sentence: Official retrospections continue as to why London 2012 <highlight>failed</highlight> to "inspire a generation."
examination_example.sentence_trans: 官方仍在反思为什么2012年伦敦奥运会未能“激励一代人”。

examination_example.sentence: The French measures have already <highlight>failed</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 法国的措施已经失败。

sense_info_list.en: grade as not passing an exam

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Failed</highlight> their college.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们大学没毕业。

examination_example.sentence: "If they <highlight>fail</highlight> first and then you fix them, it's very expensive," says Domingos.
examination_example.sentence_trans: Domingos说:“如果它们先出现故障，然后你再修复它们，那就非常昂贵了。”

word_usage.usage: 表示“没能做某事或做某事失败了”可以说fail to do sth.或fail in sth.
fail表示“衰退、衰弱”时，常用于进行时，如：Her eyesight is failing.她的视力日渐衰退。

<highlight>考纲释义</highlight>
精选实考、考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2016-2023年51套试卷，包括阅读、听力、翻译等所有题型。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>

derivative_info_list.mean: n. 失败；未做到；未履行；故障；失灵；衰退；衰竭；缺乏；不足；公司倒闭

word_family.mean: v. 失败；忘记做；坏掉；不能正常工作；破产；衰退；消失；舍弃；变弱；在（考试、测验或面试）中不及格

examination_example.sentence: Often a manager's superiors can effectively encourage a manager's distasteful behavior when they <highlight>fail</highlight> to discipline the person's wrongdoings.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 通常情况下，当管理者的上级未能对其不当行为进行惩戒时，他们会有效地鼓励管理者做出令人不快的行为。

examination_example.sentence: They <highlight>fail</highlight> to answer emails promptly.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们没有及时回复电子邮件。

examination_example.sentence: It is very likely that the CGI-recreated image of a deceased celebrity will <highlight>fail</highlight> to match the real actor especially in facial expressions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 很有可能计算机成像技术（CGI）重现的已故名人的形象无法与真正的演员相匹配，尤其是在面部表情方面。

examination_example.sentence: They are <highlight>failing</highlight> to look ahead at a time when planning for the future is more important than ever.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当规划未来比以往任何时候都更重要的时候，他们却没有向前看。

examination_example.sentence: They may <highlight>fail</highlight> to attach sufficient importance to cultural diversity.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们可能没有充分重视文化多样性。

examination_example.sentence: They may <highlight>fail</highlight> to see the cultural biases of their business partners.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们可能看不到商业合伙人的文化偏见。

sense_info_list.en: grade as not passing an exam

word_usage.usage: 在某方面失败，可直接用fail sth.表达，也可用介词in来表达：fail in sth.，介词in不可替换为其他介词。如：我所尝试的一切都失败了。I've failed (in) everything I've tried.
fail作名词时，意思是“考试不及格”，常以单数形式出现。
without fail为固定搭配，表示“务必；必定”。如：我一定把那本书带给你。I shall bring you that book without fail.

examination_example.sentence: Other times, she feels that she <highlight>fails</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 其他时候，她觉得自己失败了。

examination_example.sentence: The card reader <highlight>failed</highlight> to do the scanning.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 读卡器扫描失败。

examination_example.sentence: The store's card reader <highlight>failed</highlight> to scan the card's magnetic strip.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 商店的读卡器无法扫描卡的磁条。

examination_example.sentence: In the 20th century the main threat to international security was superpower conflict; today it is <highlight>failing</highlight> states.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在20世纪，对国际安全的主要威胁是超级大国的冲突;今天，是没落的国家。

examination_example.sentence: Indeed, even before the steep climb in grain prices in 2008, the number of <highlight>failing</highlight> states was expanding.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 事实上，甚至在2008年粮食价格急剧攀升之前，没落国家的数量就已经在扩大。

examination_example.sentence: States <highlight>fail</highlight> when governments can not provide personal security, and basic social services such as education and health care.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当政府不能提供个人安全以及基本的社会服务，如教育和卫生保健时，国家就失败了。

examination_example.sentence: The images <highlight>fail</highlight> miserably in reflecting a complicated reality.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 画面很不幸地没有反映出一个复杂的现实。

sense_info_list.en: grade as not passing an exam

examination_example.sentence: Others may experience a hopelessness that results in <highlight>failing</highlight> their core classes, such as English, science and math.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 另一些人可能会感到绝望，从而导致核心课程不及格，比如英语、科学和数学。

examination_example.sentence: Students who <highlight>fail</highlight> to finish the ninth grade with passing grades in college preparatory coursework are very unlikely to graduate on time.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 没有通过大学预科课程的学生很可能无法按时毕业。

examination_example.sentence: Without <highlight>fail</highlight> one would declare, " But I'm just not creative. "
examination_example.sentence_trans: 毫无疑问，人们会说：“但是我就是没有创造力啊。”

examination_example.sentence: If we <highlight>fail</highlight> to do so, we'll live to regret it.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果我们不这样做，我们会后悔的。

examination_example.sentence: When the result came out, I learned I <highlight>failed</highlight>!
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当结果出来后，我知道我失败了。

examination_example.sentence: Sometimes watching kids <highlight>fail</highlight> without jumping in to fix it for them is the hardest thing parents can do．
examination_example.sentence_trans: 有时候，看着孩子失败而不插手为他们解决问题是父母能做的最艰难的事情。

examination_example.sentence: These clocks were popular in the Middle East and China but they <highlight>failed</highlight> to keep accurate (精确的) time.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这些钟在中东和中国很受欢迎，但它们不能保持精确的时间。

sense_info_list.en: grade as not passing an exam

examination_example.sentence: I must prepare for the tests this time so that I won't <highlight>fail</highlight> again.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这次我必须准备考试，这样我就不会再不及格了。

examination_example.sentence: When we <highlight>fail</highlight> the exam, encouraging words from our teachers or parents make us work harder at our lessons.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当我们考试不及格时，老师或家长的鼓励话语会使我们在功课上更加努力。

examination_example.sentence: When I handed in my paper, I was afraid that I might <highlight>fail</highlight> because I did not answer the questions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当我上交试卷的时候，我担心自己可能会不及格，因为我没有回答那些问题。

examination_example.sentence: People <highlight>failed</highlight> to realize the danger of the virus.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 人们没有意识到病毒的危险。

examination_example.sentence: Those who <highlight>failed</highlight> to mark their names on the balloons were ruled out of the game.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 那些没有在气球上标明自己名字的人被淘汰出局。

examination_example.sentence: The power supply on this instrument had <highlight>failed</highlight>, so it could no longer be used.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这台仪器的电源出现了故障，因此无法再使用。

examination_example.sentence: Life <highlight>fails</highlight> us when we get into the wrong way.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当我们行差踏错时，生活会让我们感到失望。

examination_example.sentence: In 2012, Liu opened a beauty shop but <highlight>failed</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 2012年，刘开了一家美容店，但是倒闭了。
